# 詞: 睇怕

1. 睇怕今日會落大雨，你最好帶把傘先。 (It looks like it's going to rain heavily today, so you'd better bring an umbrella.)
2. 佢遲咗兩個鐘先至到，睇怕係塞車塞到癱瘓。 (He was two hours late, so it looks like the traffic was gridlocked.)
3. 呢個項目睇怕好難完成，我哋需要更多人手。 (This project looks like it will be hard to complete; we need more manpower.)
4. 睇怕佢對你冇意思，你不如早啲放棄啦。 (It looks like he's not interested in you, so you might as well give up sooner.)
5. 聽講間餐廳今晚客滿，睇怕我哋要轉去別處食飯。 (I heard the restaurant is fully booked tonight, so it looks like we'll have to go somewhere else for dinner.)
6. 睇怕你唔係真係想幫手，只係想湊熱鬧。 (It looks like you don't really want to help; you just want to join in the fun.)
7. 呢個價格睇怕太貴咗，我哋可以再搵平少少嘅。 (This price looks a bit too expensive; we can look for something a bit cheaper.)
8. 睇怕佢已經知件事，因為佢成日避開我哋。 (It looks like he already knows about the matter, because he keeps avoiding us.)
9. 天氣咁熱，睇怕泳池會好多人。 (The weather is so hot, so it looks like the pool will be very crowded.)
10. 睇怕我哋趕唔切搭尾班車，要叫的士返屋企。 (It looks like we won't make it to the last bus, so we'll have to take a taxi home.) [end of text]


